(Cheap Trick album)|Silver]]''), except the commercial failure ''[[The Doctor (Cheap Trick album)|The Doctor]]''. A reissue in 2010 described as version 3.0 added a third disc with seven additional songs.<ref>{{cite web|title=Essential 3.0|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/essential-30-r2054550|author=[[Stephen Thomas Erlewine|Erlewine, S.T.]]|publisher=[[Allmusic]]|accessdate=2011-09-05}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n===Disc 1===\nAll songs written by [[Rick Nielsen]] except as noted.\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column    = Original release\n| total_length    = \n\n| title1          = [[ELO Kiddies]]\n| note1           = Single Version\n| extra1          = ''[[Cheap Trick (1977 album)|Cheap Trick]]'' (1977)\n| length1         = 3:42\n| title2          = Hot Love\n| extra2          = ''Cheap Trick''\n| length2         = 2:31\n| title3          = [[He's a Whore]]\n| extra3          = ''Cheap Trick''\n| length3         = 2:44\n| title4          = [[Mandocello]]\n| note4           = Live, with [[Billy Corgan]]\n| extra4          = Previously Unreleased (''Cheap Trick'')\n| length4         = 5:11\n| title5          = [[Clock Strikes Ten]]\n| extra5          = ''[[In Color (album)|In Color]]'' (1977)\n| length5         = 2:59\n| title6          = [[Southern Girls]]\n| note6           = Single Version\n| writer6         = Nielsen, [[Tom Petersson]]\n| extra6          = ''In Color''\n| length6         = 3:35\n| title7          = Downed\n| extra7          = ''In Color''\n| length7         = 4:11\n| title8          = [[Hello There]]\n| extra8          = ''In Color''\n| length8         = 1:42\n| title9          = [[Surrender (Cheap Trick song)|Surrender]]\n| extra9          = ''[[Heaven Tonight]]'' (1978)\n| length9         = 4:15\n| title10          = [[California Man (song)|California Man]]\n| writer10         = [[Roy Wood]]\n| extra10          = ''Heaven Tonight''\n| length10         = 3:44\n| title11          = [[High Roller (Cheap Trick song)|High Roller]]\n| extra11       