ie |last3=Jemmy |first3=Jean-Paul |last4=Soumah |first4=Aboubacar |last5=Boum |first5=Yap |last6=Faga |first6=Elisabetta Maria |last7=Cisse |first7=Mohamed |last8=Grais |first8=Rebecca F. |title=Safety of the rVSV ZEBOV vaccine against Ebola Zaire among frontline workers in Guinea |journal=Vaccine |volume=37 |issue=48 |pages=7171\u20137177 |doi=10.1016/j.vaccine.2018.09.009 |pmid=30266489 |display-authors=3 |year=2019 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=De Nys |first1=Helene M. |last2=Kingebeni |first2=Placide Mbala |last3=Keita |first3=Alpha K. |last4=Butel |first4=Christelle |last5=Thaurignac |first5=Guillaume |last6=Villabona-Arenas |first6=Christian-Julian |last7=Lemarcis |first7=Thomas |last8=Geraerts |first8=Mare |last9=Vidal |first9=Nicole |last10=Esteban |first10=Amandine |last11=Bourgarel |first11=Mathieu |last12=Roger |first12=Fran\u00e7ois |last13=Leendertz |first13=Fabian |last14=Diallo |first14=Ramadan |last15=Ndimbo-Kumugo |first15=Simon-Pierre |last16=Nsio-Mbeta |first16=Justus |last17=Tagg |first17=Nikki |last18=Koivogui |first18=Lamine |last19=Toure |first19=Abdoulaye |last20=Delaporte |first20=Eric |last21=Ahuka-Mundeke |first21=Steve |last22=Tamfum |first22=Jean-Jacques Muyembe |last23=Mpoudi-Ngole |first23=Eitel |last24=Ayouba |first24=Ahidjo |last25=Peeters |first25=Martine |title=Survey of Ebola Viruses in Frugivorous and Insectivorous Bats in Guinea, Cameroon, and the Democratic Republic of the Congo, 2015\u20132017 |journal=Emerging Infectious Diseases |date=December 2018 |volume=24 |issue=12 |pages=2228\u20132240 |doi=10.3201/eid2412.180740 |pmid=30307845 |pmc=6256401 |display-authors=3 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Brett-Major |first1=David |last2=Lawler |first2=James |title=Catching Chances: The Movement to Be on the Ground and Research Ready before an Outbreak |journal=Viruses |date=19 August 2018 |volume=10 |issue=8 |pages=439 |doi=10.3390/v10080439 |pmid=30126221 |pmc=6116208 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Cousins |first1=Sophie |title=Violence and community mistrust hamper Ebola response |journal=The Lancet Infectious Diseases |date=December 2018 |volume=18 |issue=12 |pages=1314\u20131315 |doi=10.1016/S1473-3099(18)30658-3 |pmid=30385158 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Owens |first1=Michael D. |last2=Rice |first2=Jason |title=The Angolan Pandemic Rapid Response Team: An Assessment, Improvement, and Development Analysis of the First Self-sufficient African National Response Team Curriculum |journal=Disaster Medicine and Public Health Preparedness |volume=13 |issue=3 |pages=577\u2013581 |doi=10.1017/dmp.2018.122 |pmid=30479245 |year=2019 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Den Boon |first1=Saskia |last2=Marston |first2=Barbara J. |last3=Nyenswah |first3=Tolbert G. |last4=Jambai |first4=Amara |last5=Barry |first5=Moumie |last6=Keita |first6=Sakoba |last7=Durski |first7=Kara |last8=Senesie |first8=Schabbethai S. |last9=Perkins |first9=Devin |last10=Shah |first10=Anita |last11=Green |first11=Hugh H. |last12=Hamblion |first12=Esther L. |last13=Lamunu |first13=Margaret |last14=Gasasira |first14=Alex |last15=Mahmoud |first15=Nuha O. |last16=Djingarey |first16=Mamadou H. |last17=Morgan |first17=Oliver |last18=Crozier |first18=Ian |last19=Dye |first19=Christopher |title=Ebola Virus Infection Associated with Transmission from Survivors |journal=Emerging Infectious Diseases |date=February 2019 |volume=25 |issue=2 |pages=249\u2013255 |doi=10.3201/eid2502.181011 |pmid=30500321 |pmc=6346469 |display-authors=3 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Coltart |first1=Cordelia E. M. |last2=Lindsey |first2=Benjamin |last3=Ghinai |first3=Isaac |last4=Johnson |first4=Anne M. |last5=Heymann |first5=David L. |title=The Ebola outbreak, 2013\u20132016: old lessons for new epidemics |journal=Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society B: Biological Sciences |date=26 May 2017 |volume=372 |issue=1721 |pages=20160297 |doi=10.1098/rstb.2016.0297 |pmid=28396469 |pmc=5394636 |display-authors=3 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Okoror |first1=Lawrence |last2=Kamara |first2=Abdul |last3=Kargbo |first3=Brima |last4=Bangura |first4=James |last5=Lebby |first5=Mat |title=Transplacental transmission: A rare case of Ebola virus transmission |journal=Infectious Disease Reports |date=6 November 2018 |volume=10 |issue=3 |pages=7725 |doi=10.4081/idr.2018.7725 |pmid=30631407 |pmc=6297901 |display-authors=3 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Allegranzi |first1=Benedetta |last2=Ivanov |first2=Ivan |last3=Harrell |first3=Mason |last4=Lee |first4=Karen E. |last5=Selvaraj |first5=Saranya A. |title=Infection Rates and Risk Factors for Infection Among Health Workers During Ebola and Marburg Virus Outbreaks: A Systematic Review |journal=The Journal of Infectious Diseases |date=22 November 2018 |volume=218 |issue=suppl_5 |pages=S679\u2013S689 |doi=10.1093/infdis/jiy435 |pmid=30202878 |pmc=6249600 |display-authors=3 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Ilunga Kalenga |first1=Oly |last2=Moeti |first2=Matshidiso |last3=Sparrow |first3=Annie |last4=Nguyen |first4=Vinh-Kim |last5=Lucey |first5=Daniel |last6=Ghebreyesus |first6=Tedros A. |title=The Ongoing Ebola Epidemic in the Democratic Republic of Congo, 2018\u20132019 |journal=New England Journal of Medicine |date=29 May 2019 |volume=0 |issue=4 |pages=373\u2013383 |doi=10.1056/NEJMsr1904253 |pmid=31141654 |issn=0028-4793 |display-authors=3 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Burki |first1=Talha |title=DRC getting ready to introduce a second Ebola vaccine |journal=The Lancet. Infectious Diseases |date=November 2019 |volume=19 |issue=11 |pages=1174\u20131175 |doi=10.1016/S1473-3099(19)30577-8 |pmid=31657782 |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=DRC+getting+ready+to+introduce+a+second+Ebola+vaccine |accessdate=31 October 2019 |issn=1474-4457}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Scholia|topic}}\n*[http://www.who.int/emergencies/crises/cod/en/ World Health Organization Democratic Republic of the Congo crisis information]\n*[http://www.who.int/ebola/situation-reports/drc-2018/en/ World Health Organization Ebola situation reports]\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.msf.org.uk/ebola#Ebolatimeline|title=Ebola outbreak: timeline|publisher=M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res/Doctors Without Borders|date=2016-09-13}}\n*{{cite web |title=Ebola Virus Disease Outbreak Uganda Situation Reports |url=https://www.afro.who.int/publications/ebola-virus-disease-outbreak-uganda-situation-reports |publisher=World Health Organization (WHO) |accessdate=20 June 2019 }}\n*{{cite web |title=Genomic epidemiology of the 2018\u201319 Ebola epidemic |url=https://nextstrain.org/community/inrb-drc/ebola-nord-kivu |website=nextstrain.org |accessdate=9 November 2019}}''open source''\n*{{cite web |title=Safety and Health Topics {{!}} Ebola {{!}} Occupational Safety and Health Administration |url=https://www.osha.gov/SLTC/ebola/ |website=www.osha.gov |accessdate=9 January 2020}}\n===Video===\n[[File:Donning PPE- Perform Hand Hygiene CDC05.webm|thumb|left|110 px|Perform Hand Hygiene CDC05]]\n:::::*{{cite web |title=Donning PPE: Perform Hand Hygiene Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) {{!}} Ebola (Ebola Virus Disease) {{!}} CDC |url=https://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/hcp/ppe-training/n95Respirator_Coveralls/donning_05.html |publisher=[[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CDC) |accessdate=15 September 2018 }}\n:::::*{{cite web |title=Contact tracing/U.S. Department of Health and Human Services Centers for Disease Control and Prevention |url=https://www.cdc.gov/cdctv/EbolaContact/mpeg/EbolaContact.mp4 |publisher=[[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CDC)|accessdate=15 September 2018}}\n\n{{Subject bar|commons=y|commons-search=Ebolavirus|species=y|species-search=Filoviridae}}\n{{Ebola}}\n{{Medicine|state=collapsed}}\n{{Zoonotic viral diseases}}\n{{PHEIC}}\n{{Epidemics}} \n{{Portal bar|Africa|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kivu Ebola outbreak}}\n[[Category:2010s disease outbreaks]]\n[[Category:2020s disease outbreaks]]\n[[Category:2018 health disasters]]\n[[Category:2018 in the Democratic Republic of the Congo]]\n